# Documentation Manager Rule

## Required After Meaningful Changes
- Add a command log entry in `docs/documentation-manager/commands/`.
- Update `docs/documentation-manager/lessons-learned.md` when mistakes or corrections occurred.
- Update relevant case docs under `docs/documentation-manager/cases/`:
  - `admin/`
  - `user/`
  - `organization/`

## Command Log Requirements
- Record key commands that changed setup, schema, auth, UI, or migrations.
- Include purpose and outcome for each command.
- Do not include secrets, tokens, or private keys in logs.

## Case Documentation Requirements
- Keep each case file practical and implementation-focused.
- Note scope, routes, data model usage, and next steps.
- Reflect current state, not aspirational state.
